div.p:
If ſhe hath never ſo many Courtiers ſhe ſtudies to ſatisfy them all by feeding them with fair hopes; and when ſhe hath many in her Company, ſhe makes as if 
                     •
                  he would pleaſe them all;

Sometimes I argue from the Major to the Minor;



                        All living ſouls do feel my inſpir'd flame:



                        Then Iris too one day will do the ſame.

                   From the Minor to the Major;


Iris is ſubject to my Laws and me,



                        And ſo all other perſons too ſhall be.
